author:	benjamin boerschinger (benjamin.boerschinger@googlemail.com)
date:	06/12/12

This is the accompanying material for
BÃ¶rschinger, B., Demuth, K., and Johnson, M. "Studying the effect of input size for Bayesian Word Segmentation on the Providence Corpus", COLING 2012

for questions, please contact benjamin.boerschinger@googlemail.com

./Makefile	this is the core for running an experiment
./buildData.sh	allows you to build the transcription from scratch
./scripts/	includes scripts to prepare the data, refer to buildData.sh
./pbs/coling.sh	a front-end to run one of our experiments
./dictionary	includes the phonemic dictionaries required for transcribing the corpus
./Data		includes the corpus we used for the experiments
./Data/test1*	the held-out test-data sampled from month 22 we report on
./Data/test2*	additional held-out test-data
./testfiles	includes copies of the above files so you can re-build the data from scratch without loosing these files
./programs	programs to generate grammars, collect and evaluate Adaptor Grammar output

You will need Mark Johnson's Adaptor Grammar software, available here:
http://web.science.mq.edu.au/~mjohnson/Software.htm

If you rebuild the data, note the following:

Two utterances have been removed as they were too long, these are:

21st month of Naima:
